test_cases.objective: To verify that the user can sign in using valid credentials
test_steps: Enter a valid email address in the email field
Enter a valid password in the password field
Verify that the user is successfully logged in
expected_results: The login page appears
The email field and password field are visible
User can select either social login or email login method
User can enter a valid email address and password
Clicking on the 'Continue' button takes user to the next step
User is successfully logged in

variations.objective: To verify that social login fails if an invalid provider is selected
test_steps: Enter a valid email address in the email field
Verify that the social login fails
expected_results: The login page appears
The social login fields are visible
User can select either social login or email login method
Entering an empty value in the provider field
Clicking on the 'Continue' button should take user to the next step
Social login fails

variations.objective: To verify that email OTP fails if an invalid code is entered
test_steps: Enter a valid email address in the email field
Click on the 'Send Email Code' button
Enter an invalid code in the password field
expected_results: The login page appears
The email field and password field are visible
User can select either social login or email login method
Entering a valid email address in the email field
Clicking on the 'Send Email Code' button
Entering an empty value in the code field
Clicking on the 'Continue' button should take user to the next step
Email OTP fails

variations.objective: To verify that login page can handle edge cases
test_steps: Enter an email address with a maximum length in the email field
Verify that the email field can handle edge cases
expected_results: The login page appears

Entering an email address with a maximum length in the email field
Clicking on the 'Continue' button should take user to the next step
